@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About — Signavex</PageTitle>

<div class="animate-fade-in">
    <div class="mb-8">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface tracking-tight">About Signavex</h1>
        <p class="mt-2 text-base text-on-surface-variant max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
            Market discovery and signal analysis tool. Surfaces stocks worth investigating
            by stacking multiple confirming signals across technical, fundamental, and sentiment indicators.
        </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-on-surface-variant uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">How It Works</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 mb-8">
        <div class="rounded-[var(--radius-md)] bg-surface-container-lowest border border-outline-variant p-5">
            <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-[var(--radius-sm)] bg-primary-container text-on-primary-container mb-3">
                <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3 13.125C3 12.504 3.504 12 4.125 12h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v6.75C7.5 20.496 6.996 21 6.375 21h-2.25A1.125 1.125 0 013 19.875v-6.75zM9.75 8.625c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v11.25c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125V8.625zM16.5 4.125c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25C20.496 3 21 3.504 21 4.125v15.75c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125V4.125z" />
                </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-on-surface">10 Stock Signals</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
                Technical (MA crossover, support/resistance, trend, channel, volume), fundamental (P/E, D/E, earnings), and sentiment (news, analyst ratings).
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-[var(--radius-md)] bg-surface-container-lowest border border-outline-variant p-5">
            <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-[var(--radius-sm)] bg-tertiary-container text-on-primary-container mb-3">
                <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 21a9.004 9.004 0 008.716-6.747M12 21a9.004 9.004 0 01-8.716-6.747M12 21c2.485 0 4.5-4.03 4.5-9S14.485 3 12 3m0 18c-2.485 0-4.5-4.03-4.5-9S9.515 3 12 3m0 0a8.997 8.997 0 017.843 4.582M12 3a8.997 8.997 0 00-7.843 4.582m15.686 0A11.953 11.953 0 0112 10.5c-2.998 0-5.74-1.1-7.843-2.918m15.686 0A8.959 8.959 0 0121 12c0 .778-.099 1.533-.284 2.253m0 0A17.919 17.919 0 0112 16.5c-3.162 0-6.133-.815-8.716-2.247m0 0A9.015 9.015 0 013 12c0-1.605.42-3.113 1.157-4.418" />
                </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-on-surface">4 Market Signals</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
                Market trend, interest rates, VIX fear gauge, and sector momentum gate and scale all stock scores.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-[var(--radius-md)] bg-surface-container-lowest border border-outline-variant p-5">
            <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-[var(--radius-sm)] bg-secondary-container text-on-secondary-container mb-3">
                <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M10.5 6h9.75M10.5 6a1.5 1.5 0 11-3 0m3 0a1.5 1.5 0 10-3 0M3.75 6H7.5m3 12h9.75m-9.75 0a1.5 1.5 0 01-3 0m3 0a1.5 1.5 0 00-3 0m-3.75 0H7.5m9-6h3.75m-3.75 0a1.5 1.5 0 01-3 0m3 0a1.5 1.5 0 00-3 0m-9.75 0h9.75" />
                </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-on-surface">Configurable Weights</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
                Every signal weight is configurable. Stronger macro indicators carry more weight by default.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-on-surface-variant uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Scoring</h2>
    <div class="rounded-[var(--radius-md)] bg-surface-container-lowest border border-outline-variant p-5 mb-8 max-w-2xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Each stock is scored by evaluating all available signals. Every signal produces a score
            from <strong class="text-error">-1.0</strong> (strongly bearish) to <strong class="text-success">+1.0</strong> (strongly bullish),
            weighted by importance. The weighted average becomes the <strong class="text-on-surface">raw score</strong>.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Market-level signals (trend, rates, VIX, sector momentum) produce a <strong class="text-on-surface">market multiplier</strong>
            that scales every stock's raw score up or down. The result is the <strong class="text-on-surface">final score</strong>.
        </p>
        <div class="rounded-[var(--radius-sm)] bg-surface-container px-4 py-2.5 text-sm font-mono text-on-surface text-center">
            Final Score = Raw Score &times; Market Multiplier
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed mt-3">
            Only stocks with a final score above the surfacing threshold (0.65 for S&amp;P 500/400, 0.75 for S&amp;P 600)
            appear as candidates on the Dashboard.
        </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-on-surface-variant uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Architecture</h2>
    <div class="rounded-[var(--radius-md)] bg-surface-container-lowest border border-outline-variant p-5 max-w-2xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Scans run automatically via a background Windows Service (<strong class="text-on-surface">Signavex Worker</strong>)
            every weekday at 5:00 PM ET after market close. You can also trigger a scan manually from the Dashboard.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            This web UI is a read-only viewer over a shared SQLite database. Closing or restarting the
            web app has no effect on scheduled or in-progress scans.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
